{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883910126,"sessionID":"ses_285122fcdffeq8QOZEKmQA850l","part":{"id":"prt_d7aedf6f7001fc2VxP9xqLeSLR","messageID":"msg_d7aede3d5001qdb56Un9RNm2OM","sessionID":"ses_285122fcdffeq8QOZEKmQA850l","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_37a71ce7050540638e1b4f69","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/manifests/agentcube/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/manifests/agentcube/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC Configuration (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-031\n4: - **Module**: manifests\n5: - **Language**: YAML (Helm)\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: The RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) configuration for AgentCube provides fine-grained permission management using Kubernetes native RBAC primitives. The implementation follows the standard Kubernetes RBAC model with ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 RBAC Components\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                         AgentCube RBAC Architecture                          │\n20: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n21: │                                                                             │\n22: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n23: │  │                     ServiceAccount (SA)                             │   │\n24: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n25: │  │  │ agentcube-   │  │ agentd       │  │ workload-manager       │   │   │\n26: │  │  │ router-sa   │  │ controller-sa│  │ -sa                    │   │   │\n27: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n28: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n29: │                                    │                                         │\n30: │                                    ▼                                         │\n31: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n32: │  │                     ClusterRole / Role                              │   │\n33: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n34: │  │  │ agentcube-   │  │ agentd-      │  │ workload-manager       │   │   │\n35: │  │  │ admin        │  │ controller   │  │ -admin                 │   │   │\n36: │  │  │ (ClusterRole)│  │ (ClusterRole)│  │ (Role)                 │   │   │\n37: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n38: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n39: │                                    │                                         │\n40: │                                    ▼                                         │\n41: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n42: │  │                  ClusterRoleBinding / RoleBinding                   │   │\n43: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n44: │  │  │ agentcube-   │  │ agentd-      │  │ workload-manager       │   │   │\n45: │  │  │ router-crb  │  │ controller-  │  │ -rb                     │   │   │\n46: │  │  │              │  │ crb          │  │                          │   │   │\n47: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n48: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n49: │                                                                             │\n50: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ### 1.3 Helm Template Structure\n54: \n55: ```\n56: manifests/agentcube/\n57: ├── templates/\n58: │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml          # ServiceAccount resources\n59: │   ├── role.yaml                    # Namespace-scoped Role\n60: │   ├── rolebinding.yaml             # Namespace-scoped RoleBinding\n61: │   ├── clusterrole.yaml             # Cluster-scoped ClusterRole\n62: │   └── clusterrolebinding.yaml      # Cluster-scoped ClusterRoleBinding\n63: ├── values.yaml                      # RBAC configuration values\n64: └── Chart.yaml\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ## 2. Data Structures\n68: \n69: ### 2.1 Helm Values Schema\n70: \n71: ```yaml\n72: rbac:\n73:   # Global RBAC toggle\n74:   create: true\n75:   \n76:   # ServiceAccount configuration\n77:   serviceAccount:\n78:     create: true\n79:     name: \"\"                    # Generated if empty\n80:     annotations: {}             # Custom annotations\n81:     imagePullSecrets: []        # Image pull secrets for SA\n82:   \n83:   # Cluster-scoped Role\n84:   clusterRole:\n85:     create: true\n86:     name: \"\"                    # Generated if empty\n87:     annotations: {}             # Custom annotations\n88:     labels: {}                 # Custom labels\n89:     rules: []                  # RBAC rules\n90:   \n91:   # ClusterRoleBinding\n92:   clusterRoleBinding:\n93:     create: true\n94:     name: \"\"                    # Generated if empty\n95:     annotations: {}             # Custom annotations\n96:   \n97:   # Namespace-scoped Role (optional)\n98:   role:\n99:     create: false\n100:     name: \"\"\n101:     namespace: \"\"               # Target namespace\n102:     annotations: {}\n103:     rules: []\n104:   \n105:   # Namespace-scoped RoleBinding (optional)\n106:   roleBinding:\n107:     create: false\n108:     name: \"\"\n109:     namespace: \"\"\n110:     annotations: {}\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ### 2.2 Default RBAC Rules\n114: \n115: #### 2.2.1 AgentRuntime Controller ClusterRole\n116: \n117: ```yaml\n118: rules:\n119:   # Core resources\n120:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n121:     resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"secrets\", \"configmaps\", \"events\"]\n122:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n123:   \n124:   # AgentCube CRDs\n125:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n126:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n127:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n128:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n129:     resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n130:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n131:   \n132:   # Sandbox resources\n133:   - apiGroups: [\"sandbox.agentcube.io\"]\n134:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n135:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n136:   \n137:   # Pod management\n138:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n139:     resources: [\"pods/log\"]\n140:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n141:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n142:     resources: [\"pods/exec\"]\n143:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n144: ```\n145: \n146: #### 2.2.2 Router ServiceAccount Role\n147: \n148: ```yaml\n149: rules:\n150:   # Read-only access to resources\n151:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n152:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n153:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n154:   \n155:   # Session management\n156:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n157:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n158:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n159: ```\n160: \n161: #### 2.2.3 Workload Manager Role\n162: \n163: ```yaml\n164: rules:\n165:   # Full CRUD on sandboxes\n166:   - apiGroups: [\"sandbox.agentcube.io\"]\n167:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n168:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n169:   \n170:   # CRD management\n171:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n172:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n173:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ### 2.3 Template Data Models\n177: \n178: #### 2.3.1 ServiceAccount Template\n179: \n180: ```yaml\n181: apiVersion: v1\n182: kind: ServiceAccount\n183: metadata:\n184:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n185:   labels:\n186:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n187:   {{- with .Values.rbac.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n188:   annotations:\n189:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n190:   {{- end }}\n191: {{- with .Values.rbac.serviceAccount.imagePullSecrets }}\n192: imagePullSecrets:\n193:   {{- toYaml . | nindent 2 }}\n194: {{- end }}\n195: ```\n196: \n197: #### 2.3.2 ClusterRole Template\n198: \n199: ```yaml\n200: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n201: kind: ClusterRole\n202: metadata:\n203:   name: {{ .Values.rbac.clusterRole.name | default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n204:   labels:\n205:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n206:   {{- with .Values.rbac.clusterRole.annotations }}\n207:   annotations:\n208:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n209:   {{- end }}\n210: rules:\n211:   {{- toYaml .Values.rbac.clusterRole.rules | nindent 2 }}\n212: ```\n213: \n214: #### 2.3.3 ClusterRoleBinding Template\n215: \n216: ```yaml\n217: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n218: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n219: metadata:\n220:   name: {{ .Values.rbac.clusterRoleBinding.name | default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n221:   labels:\n222:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n223: roleRef:\n224:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n225:   kind: ClusterRole\n226:   name: {{ .Values.rbac.clusterRole.name | default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n227: subjects:\n228:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n229:     name: {{ include \"agentcube.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n230:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n231: ```\n232: \n233: #### 2.3.4 Role Template (Namespace-scoped)\n234: \n235: ```yaml\n236: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n237: kind: Role\n238: metadata:\n239:   name: {{ .Values.rbac.role.name | default (printf \"%s-%s\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) \"role\") }}\n240:   namespace: {{ .Values.rbac.role.namespace | default .Release.Namespace }}\n241:   labels:\n242:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n243: rules:\n244:   {{- toYaml .Values.rbac.role.rules | nindent 2 }}\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ## 3. API Contracts\n248: \n249: ### 3.1 ServiceAccount Resource\n250: \n251: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n252: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n253: | `apiVersion` | string | Yes | `v1` |\n254: | `kind` | string | Yes | `ServiceAccount` |\n255: | `metadata.name` | string | Yes | SA name (max 63 chars) |\n256: | `metadata.labels` | map | No | Standard labels |\n257: | `metadata.annotations` | map | No | Custom annotations |\n258: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | No | Secrets for image pull |\n259: \n260: ### 3.2 Role/ClusterRole Resource\n261: \n262: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n263: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n264: | `apiVersion` | string | Yes | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1` |\n265: | `kind` | string | Yes | `Role` or `ClusterRole` |\n266: | `metadata.name` | string | Yes | Role name |\n267: | `metadata.namespace` | string | Yes (Role only) | Namespace |\n268: | `rules` | array | Yes | Array of PolicyRule |\n269: \n270: #### PolicyRule Structure\n271: \n272: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n273: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n274: | `apiGroups` | array | Yes | API groups (e.g., `[\"\"]`, `[\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`) |\n275: | `resources` | array | Yes | Resource types (e.g., `[\"pods\"]`, `[\"agentruntimes\"]`) |\n276: | `verbs` | array | Yes | Verbs (e.g., `[\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`) |\n277: | `resourceNames` | array | No | Limit to specific resource names |\n278: | `nonResourceURLs` | array | No | Non-resource URLs (ClusterRole only) |\n279: \n280: ### 3.3 RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding Resource\n281: \n282: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n283: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n284: | `apiVersion` | string | Yes | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1` |\n285: | `kind` | string | Yes | `RoleBinding` or `ClusterRoleBinding` |\n286: | `metadata.name` | string | Yes | Binding name |\n287: | `metadata.namespace` | string | Yes (RoleBinding only) | Namespace |\n288: | `roleRef` | object | Yes | Reference to Role/ClusterRole |\n289: | `subjects` | array | Yes | Array of Subject |\n290: \n291: #### RoleRef Structure\n292: \n293: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n294: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n295: | `apiGroup` | string | Yes | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io` |\n296: | `kind` | string | Yes | `Role` or `ClusterRole` |\n297: | `name` | string | Yes | Role name |\n298: \n299: #### Subject Structure\n300: \n301: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n302: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n303: | `kind` | string | Yes | `User`, `Group`, or `ServiceAccount` |\n304: | `name` | string | Yes | Name (for SA: `sa-name` or `sa-name:namespace`) |\n305: | `apiGroup` | string | No | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io` (optional) |\n306: | `namespace` | string | No | Namespace (required for ServiceAccount) |\n307: \n308: ### 3.4 Helm Helper Functions\n309: \n310: ```yaml\n311: # _helpers.tpl\n312: \n313: {{- /*\n314: Generate ServiceAccount name\n315: */ -}}\n316: {{- define \"agentcube.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n317: {{- .Values.rbac.serviceAccount.name | default (printf \"%s-%s\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) \"sa\") }}\n318: {{- end }}\n319: \n320: {{- /*\n321: Generate ClusterRole name\n322: */ -}}\n323: {{- define \"agentcube.clusterRoleName\" -}}\n324: {{- .Values.rbac.clusterRole.name | default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n325: {{- end }}\n326: \n327: {{- /*\n328: Generate ClusterRoleBinding name\n329: */ -}}\n330: {{- define \"agentcube.clusterRoleBindingName\" -}}\n331: {{- .Values.rbac.clusterRoleBinding.name | default (printf \"%s-%s\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) \"crb\") }}\n332: {{- end }}\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ## 4. Error Handling\n336: \n337: ### 4.1 Validation Errors\n338: \n339: | Error | Scenario | Resolution |\n340: |-------|----------|------------|\n341: | Invalid ServiceAccount name | Name exceeds 63 chars | Use shorter name |\n342: | Duplicate RBAC resources | Same name in namespace | Use unique names |\n343: | Invalid rule verb | Unknown verb | Use valid K8s verbs |\n344: | Missing required field | apiGroups/resources/verbs empty | Provide required fields |\n345: | RoleBinding namespace mismatch | Role and binding different namespaces | Align namespaces |\n346: \n347: ### 4.2 Helm Validation\n348: \n349: ```bash\n350: # Validate Helm templates\n351: helm template agentcube ./manifests/agentcube --debug\n352: \n353: # Dry-run install to validate\n354: helm install --dry-run --generate-name ./manifests/agentcube\n355: \n356: # Lint Helm chart\n357: helm lint ./manifests/agentcube\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ### 4.3 RBAC Verification Commands\n361: \n362: ```bash\n363: # Check ServiceAccount\n364: kubectl get sa <sa-name> -n <namespace>\n365: \n366: # Check ClusterRole\n367: kubectl get clusterrole <role-name> -o yaml\n368: \n369: # Check RoleBinding\n370: kubectl get rolebinding <binding-name> -n <namespace> -o yaml\n371: \n372: # Verify permissions\n373: kubectl auth can-i <verb> <resource> --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:<sa-name>\n374: ```\n375: \n376: ### 4.4 Common Issues\n377: \n378: | Issue | Cause | Solution |\n379: |-------|-------|----------|\n380: | Permission denied | Missing RBAC rules | Add required verbs to Role/ClusterRole |\n381: | Resource not found | Wrong namespace | Specify correct namespace in Subject |\n382: | Role not bound | Missing RoleBinding | Create RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding |\n383: | Orphaned binding | Role deleted before binding | Delete orphaned binding manually |\n384: \n385: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n386: \n387: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n388: \n389: #### 5.1.1 Template Rendering Test\n390: \n391: ```python\n392: def test_rbac_serviceaccount_template():\n393:     \"\"\"Test ServiceAccount template renders correctly.\"\"\"\n394:     values = {\n395:         \"rbac\": {\n396:             \"create\": True,\n397:             \"serviceAccount\": {\n398:                 \"name\": \"test-sa\",\n399:                 \"annotations\": {\"test\": \"annotation\"},\n400:                 \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"regcred\"}]\n401:             }\n402:         }\n403:     }\n404:     # Verify template renders with correct values\n405: ```\n406: \n407: #### 5.1.2 Template Conditional Test\n408: \n409: ```python\n410: def test_rbac_disabled():\n411:     \"\"\"Test templates are skipped when RBAC is disabled.\"\"\"\n412:     values = {\"rbac\": {\"create\": False}}\n413:     # Verify no RBAC resources are rendered\n414: ```\n415: \n416: #### 5.1.3 Rule Validation Test\n417: \n418: ```python\n419: def test_clusterrole_rules():\n420:     \"\"\"Test ClusterRole rules are valid.\"\"\"\n421:     rules = [\n422:         {\n423:             \"apiGroups\": [\"\"],\n424:             \"resources\": [\"pods\"],\n425:             \"verbs\": [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n426:         }\n427:     ]\n428:     # Verify rule structure is valid\n429: ```\n430: \n431: ### 5.2 Integration Tests\n432: \n433: #### 5.2.1 Helm Install Test\n434: \n435: ```bash\n436: # Install chart with RBAC\n437: helm install agentcube ./manifests/agentcube --namespace agentcube\n438: \n439: # Verify resources\n440: kubectl get sa,clusterrole,clusterrolebinding -n agentcube\n441: \n442: # Verify permissions\n443: kubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-sa\n444: ```\n445: \n446: #### 5.2.2 RBAC Verification Test\n447: \n448: ```bash\n449: # Test controller permissions\n450: kubectl auth can-i get agentruntimes --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentd-sa\n451: # Expected: yes\n452: \n453: # Test router permissions  \n454: kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:router-sa\n455: # Expected: no (read-only)\n456: ```\n457: \n458: ### 5.3 Helm Test Suite\n459: \n460: ```yaml\n461: # tests/rbac_test.yaml\n462: suite: RBAC tests\n463: tests:\n464:   - name: serviceaccount-creation\n465:     chart: ./manifests/agentcube\n466:     release: test-rbac\n467:     namespace: test-rbac\n468:     asserts:\n469:       - equal:\n470:           path: metadata.name\n471:           value: agentcube-sa\n472:       - present:\n473:           path: metadata.labels.app.kubernetes.io/name\n474:   \n475:   - name: clusterrole-creation\n476:     asserts:\n477:       - equal:\n478:           path: rules[0].resources\n479:           value: [pods, services]\n480:   \n481:   - name: clusterrolebinding-subjects\n482:     asserts:\n483:       - equal:\n484:           path: subjects[0].kind\n485:           value: ServiceAccount\n486: ```\n487: \n488: ### 5.4 Build Verification\n489: \n490: ```bash\n491: # Template validation\n492: helm template agentcube ./manifests/agentcube > /dev/null\n493: \n494: # Dry-run install\n495: helm install --dry-run test ./manifests/agentcube\n496: \n497: # Lint chart\n498: helm lint ./manifests/agentcube\n499: \n500: # Verify RBAC manifests\n501: kubeval manifests/agentcube/templates/*.yaml\n502: ```\n503: \n504: ## 6. Usage Examples\n505: \n506: ### 6.1 Default Installation\n507: \n508: ```bash\n509: # Install with default RBAC\n510: helm install agentcube ./manifests/agentcube --namespace agentcube --create-namespace\n511: \n512: # Verify RBAC resources\n513: kubectl get sa,clusterrole,clusterrolebinding -n agentcube\n514: ```\n515: \n516: ### 6.2 Custom ServiceAccount\n517: \n518: ```bash\n519: # Install with custom SA name\n520: helm install agentcube ./manifests/agentcube \\\n521:   --set rbac.serviceAccount.name=my-custom-sa \\\n522:   --namespace agentcube\n523: ```\n524: \n525: ### 6.3 Additional RBAC Rules\n526: \n527: ```bash\n528: # Install with additional rules\n529: helm install agentcube ./manifests/agentcube \\\n530:   --set rbac.clusterRole.rules[0].apiGroups[0]= \\\n531:   --set rbac.clusterRole.rules[0].resources[0]=namespaces \\\n532:   --set rbac.clusterRole.rules[0].verbs[0]=get \\\n533:   --namespace agentcube\n534: ```\n535: \n536: ### 6.4 Disable RBAC\n537: \n538: ```bash\n539: # Install without RBAC resources\n540: helm install agentcube ./manifests/agentcube \\\n541:   --set rbac.create=false \\\n542:   --namespace agentcube\n543: ```\n544: \n545: ## 7. Configuration Reference\n546: \n547: ### 7.1 Full Values Example\n548: \n549: ```yaml\n550: rbac:\n551:   create: true\n552:   \n553:   serviceAccount:\n554:     create: true\n555:     name: \"agentcube-controller\"\n556:     annotations:\n557:       \"eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn\": \"arn:aws:iam::123456789:role/agentcube-role\"\n558:     imagePullSecrets:\n559:       - name: \"regcred\"\n560:   \n561:   clusterRole:\n562:     create: true\n563:     name: \"agentcube-controller\"\n564:     annotations:\n565:       \"description\": \"AgentCube controller ClusterRole\"\n566:     rules:\n567:       - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n568:         resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"secrets\", \"configmaps\", \"events\"]\n569:         verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n570:       - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n571:         resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n572:         verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n573:       - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n574:         resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n575:         verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n576:   \n577:   clusterRoleBinding:\n578:     create: true\n579:     name: \"agentcube-controller-binding\"\n580:     annotations:\n581:       \"description\": \"AgentCube controller ClusterRoleBinding\"\n582:   \n583:   role:\n584:     create: false\n585:   \n586:   roleBinding:\n587:     create: false\n588: ```\n589: \n590: ---\n591: \n592: *Stage ST-1 completed*\n\n(End of file - total 592 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC Configuration (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-031\n- **Module**: manifests\n- **Language**: YAML (Helm)\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) configuration for AgentCube provides fine-grained permission management using Kubernetes native RBAC primitives. The implementation follows the standard Kubernetes RBAC model with ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources.\n\n### 1.2 RBAC Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         AgentCube RBAC Architecture                          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/manifests/agentcube/design.md","time":{"start":1775883910065,"end":1775883910123}}}}
